---
// FAQ section component
const faqs = [
  {
    question: "How accurate is Quick2query's natural language to SQL translation?",
    answer: "Quick2query utilizes advanced AI models achieving over 95% accuracy in SQL translation. Our system continuously learns from usage patterns and validates queries before execution to ensure data integrity. The AI understands complex business context and can handle nested queries, joins, and advanced SQL operations with high precision."
  },
  {
    question: "What databases does Quick2query support?",
    answer: "We support all major SQL databases including PostgreSQL, MySQL, Microsoft SQL Server, Oracle, and SQLite. Our API provides consistent results across different database systems while optimizing queries for each specific database engine's capabilities and syntax variations."
  },
  {
    question: "How secure is Quick2query with sensitive data?",
    answer: "Security is our top priority. We implement enterprise-grade security measures including end-to-end encryption, role-based access control, and detailed audit logging. Our API never stores your data - it only processes queries and returns results. We're SOC 2 Type II certified and comply with GDPR and other data protection regulations."
  },
  {
    question: "Can Quick2query integrate with our existing data tools?",
    answer: "Yes, Quick2query offers robust REST API integration capabilities and works seamlessly with popular BI tools, data visualization platforms, and custom applications. We provide comprehensive SDKs for major programming languages and detailed documentation to ensure smooth integration with your existing data stack."
  },
  {
    question: "What kind of support and SLA do you provide?",
    answer: "We provide 24/7 technical support with 99.9% uptime SLA for all enterprise plans. Our support team includes both AI and database experts who understand complex data challenges. Enterprise customers get dedicated solution architects and priority response times under 1 hour."
  },
  {
    question: "How can we try Quick2query?",
    answer: "We offer a free API key with 100 queries/month to test our service. For businesses, we provide a 14-day full-access trial with unlimited queries and all enterprise features. Our team will help you set up a proof-of-concept with your actual data to demonstrate the value Quick2query can bring to your organization."
  }
];
---

<section id="faq" class="section-padding bg-white py-24">
  <div class="container-custom">
    <div class="text-center mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-indigo-950 mb-6 font-primary">Common Questions About Our API</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed font-secondary">
        Learn more about Quick2query's natural language to SQL capabilities and how it can transform your data analysis workflow.
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-4">
      {faqs.map((faq, index) => (
        <div class="faq-item bg-white border border-background rounded-2xl overflow-hidden shadow-sm hover:shadow-md transition-all duration-300">
          <button class="faq-question w-full text-left">
            <span class="text-xl font-bold text-text font-primary">{faq.question}</span>
            <svg class="faq-icon w-6 h-6 text-tech" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
            </svg>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer hidden">
            <p class="text-text leading-relaxed text-lg font-secondary">{faq.answer}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
